# Knowledge Base & Continuous Documentation

## Golden rule: Read before you write
Before implementing any change, **consult the relevant step README** in `steps/step-XX-name/README.md`. These files contain:
- Design decisions and their rationale
- Known limitations and workarounds
- Troubleshooting guides from real deployments
- Official documentation references

## Knowledge sources in this repo

| Source | Purpose | When to consult |
|--------|---------|-----------------|
| `README.md` (root) | Project overview, quick start | Understanding overall architecture |
| `steps/step-XX/README.md` | Step-specific deep knowledge | Before modifying that step |
| Troubleshooting sections | Known issues and solutions | When debugging failures |
| References sections | Official doc links | When validating YAML/APIs |
| `docs/alignment-evidence-ledger.md` | Pre-merge product-doc alignment evidence | Before merging GitOps component changes |
| `/Users/adrina/Sandbox/rh-brain/Red Hat Brain` | Read-only Red Hat article/wiki research corpus | When improving step README narrative and Red Hat article alignment |

## Enhance documentation when you learn something new

When resolving an issue or discovering a pattern, **update the relevant README**:

### 1. Troubleshooting discoveries
Add new issues to the Troubleshooting section:
```markdown
### <Symptom/Error Message>

**Root Cause:** <explanation>

**Solution:**
```bash
<fix commands>
```
```

### 2. Design decisions
Document "why" not just "what":
```markdown
> **Design Decision:** We use X instead of Y because...
```

### 3. Workarounds for known limitations
If something doesn't work as expected with RHOAI 3.4 or RHOCP 4.20:
```markdown
> **Known Limitation (RHOAI 3.4):** <description>
> **Workaround:** <solution>
> **Ref:** <link to issue/KB article if available>
```

### 4. Version-specific notes
Tag version-sensitive information:
```markdown
> **Note (RHOAI 3.4 / RHOCP 4.20):** This behavior may change in future versions.
```

## Cross-reference related steps
When changes in one step affect another, add cross-references:
```markdown
> **See also:** [Step 03 - Private AI](../step-03-private-ai/README.md)
```

## Keep the knowledge base growing
- Every bug fix is an opportunity to document a troubleshooting entry
- Every workaround is a design decision worth explaining
- Every deployment validates (or corrects) existing documentation
- Every question asked twice should become documentation
- Every GitOps component change should refresh the alignment evidence ledger

## Official docs remain the source of truth
- README knowledge supplements, not replaces, official documentation
- Always link to official RHOAI 3.4 / RHOCP 4.20 docs
- When official docs conflict with our implementation, note it explicitly and explain why
- Use `rh-brain` only for research-backed narrative and article alignment; do not treat it as product configuration authority
